    "Html": "<br>\r\nThanks Ben,<br>\r\n<br>\r\nI have already resolved the issue of having only the item placeholder row.. However the ItemsControl still displays the item regarding the placeholder row...<br>\r\n<br>\r\nI think it is kind of a wierd behaviour... although I do understand the need to have a placeholder row, the corresponding item should be &quot;invisible&quot; (temporary..whatever) or not available to other WPF objects (like .. in this case the ItemsControl)...<br>\r\n<br>\r\nIs there a workaround for this? like setting the ItemsControl &quot;extra&quot; item visibility to hidden?<br>\r\n<br>\r\nThanks in advance<br>\r\n",
